@metroid manga, doujin and doujinshi are not mutually exclusive. Manga is a Japanese style of comic, which is the most obvious word you mentioned. Doujin (同人) is made of of the kanji for "same" and "person", and is used broadly to refer to a group of people with similar interests but is used generally to refer to self published works within communities. Doujinshi (同人誌), is the same kanji as doujin but with the kanji from magazine (雑誌) tacked onto the end to refer to self published books/manga. As such, the previous commenters were right in calling this a doujin and your comments were kinda dumb lmao
